  "texts": [
    "Sometimes these sub-themes were raised together, for instanced \"students need to complete all assessments in an examination situation and in pen to paper\".",
    "Other suggested assessment task types included video production or visual essay (n = 7) and portfolio (n = 3).",
    "Respondents identified that changes to the types of content included in assessment were warranted to address AI issues.",
    "A large number of respondents identified that assessment tasks needed to be inclined towards higher-order thinking (n = 71), including \"critical thinking and application\" and \"evaluation-type questions\".",
    "Other suggestions were shifts towards more authentic tasks (n = 65) and focus on the process of assessment (n = 50) like \"incorporating a lot more process-driven methodologies (drafting, research booklets etc.)\"."
